# Git LFS — track binary asset files outside the regular Git object store.
#
# Prerequisites (one-time per developer):
#   brew install git-lfs       # macOS, or apt-get install git-lfs on Linux
#   git lfs install            # installs hooks in this repo's .git/
# After that, normal `git add` / `git commit` / `git push` works as usual —
# Git automatically routes matched files to LFS based on the rules below.
# Existing committed binaries before this file was added are NOT migrated;
# they stay in regular Git history. Going forward, new binary commits use LFS.
# To migrate existing assets/ files into LFS retroactively:
#   git lfs migrate import --include="assets/**" --everything
# (rewrites history — coordinate with anyone else who has a clone)

# Images
*.png  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpg  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.webp filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.gif  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.tga  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.bmp  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Audio
*.ogg  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mp3  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.wav  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.flac filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.opus filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Video (Demo Creator artifacts, eventually)
*.mp4  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.webm filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mov  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Fonts (game-owned, under assets/ — vendored addon fonts are excluded below)
*.ttf  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.otf  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.woff filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.woff2 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Godot binary exports
*.pck  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
assets/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vendored third-party addons (e.g. the GUT test framework) — keep as PLAIN Git
# objects, NOT LFS. This rule is LAST so it overrides the *.ttf / *.png rules
# above for anything under addons/.
#
# WHY: GUT ships tiny binary fonts (addons/gut/fonts/*.ttf). Under an LFS filter
# they became perpetually "not uptodate" in git's eyes, which made worktree
# tree-switches (git checkout/reset --force) refuse with "Entry '…ttf' not
# uptodate. Cannot merge." — wedging clean_slate and death-looping a worker.
# These files are small and rarely change, so plain Git is correct and avoids
# the wedge entirely. See docs/WORKER_OPERATIONS.md §1.
addons/** -filter -diff -merge -text
